  "body": "So, bigNumber is a common way to represent values from solidity smart contracts. However, I can't use BigNubmer comparisons as stated here by default: https://www.chaijs.com/plugins/chai-bignumber/ \r\n\r\n\r\nI would like to be able to do something like:\r\n```js\r\nexpect(afterBalance).to.be.bignumber.greaterThan(beforeBalance);\r\n```\r\nwithout having to add `chai-bignumber` to a hardhat project and set it up. Given that BigNumber is so common, it does not make sense to me for comparisons between this type not coming out of the box in hardhat.\r\n\r\nAt least some documentation regarding on how to set it up should be added.\r\n",
