    "body": "I don't think that works. Note that `chai-bignumber` is built for `bignumber.js`, and ethers has its custom big number class with a different api.\r\n\r\nFor example, this\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst chai = require(\"chai\");\r\nconst ethers = require(\"ethers\");\r\nchai.use(require('chai-bignumber')(ethers.BigNumber));\r\n\r\nchai.expect(ethers.constants.One).to.be.equal(ethers.BigNumber.from(1));\r\n```\r\n\r\nThrows this\r\n\r\n```\r\nnode index.js\r\n\r\n/private/tmp/npmproject-0/node_modules/chai/lib/chai/assertion.js:152\r\n      throw new AssertionError(\r\n      ^\r\nAssertionError: expected { Object (_hex, _isBigNumber) } to equal { Object (_hex, _isBigNumber) }\r\n    at Object.<anonymous> (/private/tmp/npmproject-0/index.js:5:41)\r\n    at Module._compile (node:internal/modules/cjs/loader:1101:14)\r\n    at Object.Module._extensions..js (node:internal/modules/cjs/loader:1153:10)\r\n    at Module.load (node:internal/modules/cjs/loader:981:32)\r\n    at Function.Module._load (node:internal/modules/cjs/loader:822:12)\r\n    at Function.executeUserEntryPoint [as runMain] (node:internal/modules/run_main:79:12)\r\n    at node:internal/main/run_main_module:17:47 {\r\n  showDiff: true,\r\n  actual: BigNumber { _hex: '0x01', _isBigNumber: true },\r\n  expected: BigNumber { _hex: '0x01', _isBigNumber: true },\r\n  operator: 'deepStrictEqual'\r\n}\r\n```",
